        "title": "Catechol-Aluminum Coordination Network with Rigid Polybenzoxazine Backbone",
        "what_it_is": "Combine catechol-metal coordination chemistry—inspired by mussel byssus threads—with a high-Tg polybenzoxazine backbone. Synthesize benzoxazine monomers with pendant catechol groups (dopamine-benzoxazine or caffeic acid-benzoxazine). Cure produces the polybenzoxazine backbone (Tg >200°C from rigid aromatic structure) with pendant catechol groups available for metal coordination.\n\nPost-cure treatment with Al3+ (from aluminum acetylacetonate or aluminum isopropoxide at 100-150°C) forms tris-catechol-Al3+ coordination crosslinks. Each catechol-Al interaction contributes 40-80 kJ/mol; the tris complex totals 120-240 kJ/mol—approaching covalent C-C bond strength. These coordination bonds are kinetically stable at neutral pH but dissociate rapidly at pH 2-4.\n\nFor recycling, immersion in 0.1M HCl at room temperature protonates catechol groups, releasing Al3+ and fragmenting the network. Fibers are released as the matrix dissolves. The recycling conditions are remarkably mild: room temperature, dilute food-grade acid, complete dissolution in hours.",
        "why_it_works": "Catechol (1,2-benzenediol) forms a bidentate chelate with Al3+ through both oxygen atoms. At neutral pH, catechol is deprotonated (effective pKa lowered by metal coordination) and binding is extremely strong—log K ~37 for the tris complex. At pH <4, protonation competes with metal binding; at pH <2, catechol is fully protonated and Al3+ is released as soluble AlCl3.\n\nThe equilibrium shifts cleanly with pH: 3 Cat2- + Al3+ ⇌ [Al(Cat)3]3-. This is completely orthogonal to temperature—you can have Tg >200°C with recycling at room temperature. No thermal trigger can accidentally cleave the bonds during service.",
        "why_this_one": "The pH trigger is genuinely orthogonal to service conditions in a way that thermal triggers are not. Diels-Alder retro-reaction at 120°C overlaps with service; vitrimer exchange at 180°C overlaps with service. But pH 2-4 cannot occur inside an aircraft structure. This provides the cleanest separation between service and recycling conditions of any approach we evaluated."
